Amazing poke, pay by the plate or by the weight. I stopped by here because it's next door to Itchy Butt Korean Fried Chicken.  I had the famous "Ono Seafood Poke" the day before and was underwhelmed to say the least.  This poke here put all my faith back into the fact that Oahu does poke best.  I got 5 different kinds that day (sorry, I did not get photos of the shoyu poke, which actually was my favorite, or the spicy salmon, which looks just like the mayonaisey spicy ahi pictured below).   The one covered in masago was amazing.  Every piece of tuna was glistening with the roe.  And by every piece I mean all the poke here is cut into cubes for texture.  You won't find mashed up ahi or salmon here. They were out of yellowtail so I was bummed out.  The spicy ahi was rich and creamy, but not too spicy to take away from the real flavor. You can always add more with condiments.  The tako (octopus) was cut thin and cooked perfectly. It had the snap and texture well prepared tako deserves. I got the Hawaiian style, which includes some "ogo" limu. The limu texture really makes the tako pop even more, similar to how the masago reacts with the tuna.   Lastly, the shoyu ahi is most likely their most popular, because there were two tubs of it.  White onion, and bite sized cubes of fresh ahi marinated in the shoyu sauce was my favorite.  Each piece was so fresh, so flavorful, slightly sweet and salty, with the bite of onion to balance it...oooof.  I literally finished over a pound of poke and a huge bowl of rice and couldn't eat for the rest of the day.  My fave.
